               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170115-44-person339">
                  ANTONIO 
                  FRANCALANZA
               <interp inst="t18170115-44-person339" type="surname" value="FRANCALANZA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170115-44-person339" type="given" value="ANTONIO"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170115-44-person339" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Leicester-square, and am a <rs id="t18170115-44-viclabel222" type="occupation">fencing-master</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170115-44-victim338 t18170115-44-viclabel222"></join>. On the 8th of January, between two and three o'clock in the afternoon, I was at the top of <placeName id="t18170115-44-crimeloc223">Holborn</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18170115-44-crimeloc223" type="placeName" value="Holborn"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18170115-44-crimeloc223" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170115-44-off220 t18170115-44-crimeloc223"></join>, near St. Giles's; I felt somebody at my pocket; I turned round and saw the prisoner putting something in his breast. I took hold of his hand, my handkerchief was in his breast. I secured him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170115-44-person340">
                  BENJAMIN 
                  WINTER
               <interp inst="t18170115-44-person340" type="surname" value="WINTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170115-44-person340" type="given" value="BENJAMIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170115-44-person340" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was going down Holborn, between two and three o'clock, in the afternoon, on the 8th of January. I saw the prisoner take the handkerchief out of the prosecutor's pocket; the prosecutor seized him, and I ran over to his assistance. His friends attempted to get him away, but I would not let them.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
